{
  "verses": [
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "text": [
        "Job Prepares His Case"
      ]
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "1",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "“Indeed, my eyes have seen all this; my ears have heard and understood."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "2",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "What you know, I also know; I am not inferior to you."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "3",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Yet I desire to speak to the Almighty and argue my case before God."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "4",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You, however, smear with lies; you are all worthless physicians."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "5",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "If only you would remain silent; for that would be your wisdom!"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "6",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Hear now my argument, and listen to the plea of my lips."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "7",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Will you speak wickedly on God’s behalfor speak deceitfully for Him?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "8",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Would you show Him partialityor argue in His defense?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "9",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Would it be well when He examined you? Could you deceive Him like a man?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "10",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Surely He would rebuke youif you secretly showed partiality."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "11",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Would His majesty not terrify you? Would the dread of Him not fall upon you?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "12",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Your maxims are proverbs of ashes; your defenses are defenses of clay."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "13",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Be silent, and I will speak. Then let come to me what may."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "14",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Why do I put myself at risk[^20] and take my life in my own hands?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "15",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Though He slay me, I will hope in Him.[^21] I will still defend my ways to His face."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "16",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Moreover, this will be my salvation, for no godless man can appear before Him."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "17",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Listen carefully to my words; let my declaration ring in your ears."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "18",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Behold, now that I have prepared my case, I know that I will be vindicated."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "19",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Can anyone indict me? If so, I will be silent and die."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "20",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Only grant these two things to me, so that I need not hide from You:"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "21",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Withdraw Your hand from me, and do not let Your terror frighten me."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "22",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Then call me, and I will answer, or let me speak, and You can reply."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "23",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "How many are my iniquities and sins? Reveal to me my transgression and sin."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "24",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Why do You hide Your face and consider me as Your enemy?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "25",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "Would You frighten a windblown leaf? Would You chase after dry chaff?"
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "26",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "For You record bitter accusations against me and bequeath to me the iniquities of my youth."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "27",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "You put my feet in the stocks and st and watch over all my paths; You set a limitfor the soles of my feet."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    },
    {
      "verse_num": "28",
      "segments": [
        {
          "type": "narrative",
          "text": "So man wastes away like something rotten, like a moth-eaten garment."
        }
      ],
      "footnotes": [],
      "references": []
    }
  ]
}